              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="tip-card tip-card--warning">
              <div class="tip-number">52</div>
              <div class="tip-body">
                <h3>Thumping sound — check for foreign objects first</h3>
                <p>A rhythmic thumping often means a coin, button, or small object bouncing in the drum or caught in the drum seal. Check pockets before every load. If the drum is empty and thumping continues, it's likely worn drum rollers.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="tip-card tip-card--warning">
              <div class="tip-number">53</div>
              <div class="tip-body">
                <h3>Clothes taking longer than usual to dry</h3>
                <p>Extended drying times are the first and most reliable symptom of a clogged exhaust duct. Check that the outdoor vent is blowing air freely while the dryer runs. If not — the duct needs cleaning. Don't ignore this symptom.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="tip-card">
              <div class="tip-number">54</div>
              <div class="tip-body">
                <h3>Check pockets before every single load</h3>
                <p>Coins damage the drum and create thumping. Pens leave permanent ink stains. Gum and candy melt onto the drum interior. Lip balm and chapstick grease the drum and transfer to all clothing. 30 seconds checking pockets prevents all of these.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="tip-card">
              <div class="tip-number">55</div>
              <div class="tip-body">
